node.text:
Caption this!👇Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on nomadfervor.com (link in my bio: @nomadfervor)

The teeterboard (or Korean plank) is an acrobatic apparatus that resembles a playground seesaw. The strongest teeterboards are made of oak (usually 9 feet in length). The board is divided in the middle by a fulcrum made of welded steel. At each end of the board is a square padded area, where a performer stands on an incline before being catapulted into the air. The well-trained flyer performs various aerial somersaults, landing on padded mats, a human pyramid, a specialized landing chair, stilts, or even a Russian bar.

The teeterboard is operated by a team of flyers, catchers, spotters and pushers. Some members of the team perform more than one acrobatic role. In the early 1960s the finest teeterboard acts, trained in the Eastern Bloc countries, performed with Ringling Brothers and Barnum & Bailey Circus.

📽 @osguriteeterboard
📍Pelotas, Brazil
🎶 Bipolar - Mc Davi, Mc Pedrinho, Mc Don Juan

node.text:
Would you dare to walk on this Via Ferrata? 😳 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @nomadfervor 

The new Signora Delle Acque, in the Ruzza river, is a highly emotional and spectacular via ferrata that gives you unforgettable emotions; the sight embraces whole Trentino, but keeping fixed on the track too.

📽 @niklaskoessel
📍Trentino, Italy

node.text:
The world’s biggest cat 🦁You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @nomadfervor

It’s a Liger, a hybrid offspring of a male lion and a female tiger. It has parents in the same genus but of different species. Distinct from the similar hybrid tigon, and is the largest of all known extant felines. 🐾

📽 @docantle w/ @kodyantle
